I did my eyes closed during the entire beginning and end of today's practice because I trusted you enough to walk me through it. I feel a lot calmer doing that but I also wanted to answer about release. In thinking about what I need to release or let go from my life, as I'm a writer, I thought it was going to be one of my many projects that are in a process of editing / rewriting. However, as I deepened my breath and reflected, my mind came to a person I know who I used to be friends with and now all I see is a ball of bouncing negativity. I didn't come today thinking that would be my release, but as I think about it off the mat and how I tense even if she likes something of mine on Facebook, I have to let her go. I have to defriend, I have to take a step back, and let her go. Maybe one of these days, I'll want her back but I don't need that in my life right now. I beat myself and can be a bouncing ball of negativity all on my own sometimes and I don't need another person being it. So, in an odd sort of way, thank you for helping me find my release even though it's sort of bittersweet, it's better for me in the long run. <3
